  "prompt": "Who is the fastest footballer in the world?",
  "response": "The title of the fastest footballer in the world can vary depending on the criteria used for measurement, such as top sprint speed or average running speed during a game. As of recent years, players like Kylian Mbapp\u00e9, Adama Traor\u00e9, and Alphonso Davies have been frequently mentioned in discussions about speed due to their exceptional sprinting abilities.\n\nKylian Mbapp\u00e9, for instance, has been recorded reaching speeds of up to 36 km/h (22.4 mph), which is among the highest recorded in professional football.\n\nAlphonso Davies has shown impressive speed as well, especially during his standout performance in the UEFA Champions League for Bayern Munich. He's been clocked at speeds up to 35.3 km/h (21.9 mph).\n\nAdama Traor\u00e9 is renowned for his explosive pace and strength, regularly making rapid sprints that leave defenders trailing behind.\n\nAs measurements and rankings can change with new data and performances, it\u2019s always good to check the latest statistics and speed tests for the most current information.",
